## Open Questions

- **Pipe Height**: Should pipes be assumed to be at floor level, ceiling level (under-joist), or mid-wall? I propose a default "Mounting Height" property in the inspector.
- **Auto-Routing**: Should the pipe builder try to avoid walls or go through them? (Initial version: straight lines, user manual control).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No automated tests currently exist in the repo. I will perform manual verification.

### Manual Verification
- **Multi-floor check**: Draw walls on Floor 1, switch to Floor 2, verify Floor 1 is visible as a ghost.
- **Pipe Builder check**: Draw a refrigerant line from an indoor Air Handler to an outdoor Condenser. Verify it appears in 3D.
- **Layer Control check**: Hide "HVAC" layer and ensure all units and pipes (if assigned to HVAC layer) disappear.
- **3D Slab check**: Open 3D viewer and verify distinct floor levels with slabs.
